The paper focuses on machine learning techniques applied to security games, which are a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The use of machine learning implies the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper deals with security and the modeling of attackers, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the estimation of attacker payoffs, which is a problem that can be tackled with machine learning algorithms such as regression (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions online learning techniques, which are a subfield of machine learning and can be applied to various domains, including security (cs.SI).
